trailingComments.value:
*
* An absolute path. We consider tilde paths (those starting with '~') to be
* absolute because they don't depend on the current working directory.
* 
* Note that this is different than the Node `path` module's [isAbsolute][],
* which returns `false` for tilde paths.
* 
* [isAbsolute]: https://nodejs.org/api/path.html#path_path_isabsolute_path
* 
* We represent that behavior with {@link ResolvedPath}.
* 
* @typedef {string} AbsPath

*
* An absolute path. We consider tilde paths (those starting with '~') to be
* absolute because they don't depend on the current working directory.
* 
* Note that this is different than the Node `path` module's [isAbsolute][],
* which returns `false` for tilde paths.
* 
* [isAbsolute]: https://nodejs.org/api/path.html#path_path_isabsolute_path
* 
* We represent that behavior with {@link ResolvedPath}.
* 
* @typedef {string} AbsPath
